[1]
Date: Thu 1 Sep 2022
Source: Al Arabiya [edited]
https://english.alarabiya.net/News/world/2022/09/01/Third-person-dies-of-mystery-pneumonia-in-Argentina


A 3rd person died this week in Argentina from pneumonia of unknown origin, local health authorities said on Thursday [1 Sep 2022].

Nine people in northwestern Tucuman province have been infected by the mysterious respiratory illness, including 8 medical staff at the same private clinic, and 3 have died since Monday [29 Aug 2022], Tucuman health minister Luis Medina Ruiz told reporters.

Authorities are conducting tests on the illness, but Medina said they have ruled out COVID, flu and influenza types A and B. Samples have been sent to the prestigious Malbran Institute in Buenos Aires.

The 3rd victim was a 70-year-old patient admitted to the same clinic where staff have been infected, ahead of a surgical procedure. Medina said the woman could have been "patient zero, but that is being evaluated."

The 1st patient died on Monday [29 Aug 2022] and the 2nd on Wednesday [31 Aug 2022].

Medina said on Wednesday [31 Aug 2022] the patients were suffering from "a severe respiratory condition with bilateral pneumonia ... very similar to COVID."

Experts were analyzing the local water and air conditioners to see if it was a case of poisoning, while Medina said it could also be due to an infection.

The 1st 6 patients started exhibiting symptoms between [18 and 22 Aug 2022].

Of the last 3 cases, 2 are receiving hospital treatment and 1 is being monitored at home.

